Segun Olaniyan Katsina – The Kaduna/Katsina Customs Area Command has collected the sum of N852, 064,139.41 in the month of August in compliance with its mandate of service on revenue generation. Abdulrazak Oyeleke, the Command Area Comptroller revealed this at a press briefing held in Katsina on Tuesday. Oyeleke said the amount surpassed the monthly target with the sum of over N342 million, adding that, “this amount surpasses the preceding months based on the monthly revenue target.” According to him, on anti-smuggling for the period under review, 81 seizures worth over N32.7 million of duty paid value DPV was made by the command. The Customs boss added that the seized items include, 606 bags of foreign rice, 239 bags of imported sugar, 73 bales of second hand clothing, 327 Jerry cans of vegetable oil, 28 motor vehicles of various kind and two motorcycles. This efforts, he said, was in tandem with the efforts of the customs intelligence unit CIU and other units of the command across the state. Oyeleke, however, appealed to Nigerians, particularly parents, the clergy and traditional rulers to admonish their children and members against the evils of smuggling on the nation’s economy and lend support to the policies of the Federal government on rice farming. “They should rather support the Federal government policy on rice planting as this will create more jobs for the citizenry and boost the nation’s economy”, he concluded. SHOCKING STORY!!! After 9 Years Of Suffering From Weak Erection & Premature Ejaculation, 43 Year Old Man Finally Discovers The Solution That Mysteriously Jerk His Dead Manhood Back To Life, Increased His "Rod" Size, And Now Last 32 Minutes In Bed. Click HERE! 